description: “Prociono” (pro-tsee-O-no) is an Esperanto word meaning either the star Procyon or the animal species known as the raccoon. It is a roman with blackletter elements. The font is also available from the designer's own site, Sortmill, with a public domain dedication instead of the SIL Open Font License, and is also available from the League of Movable Type.
